# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Phase 5c: Method Replicate Decision — SHARK-capture
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

--- 2026-06-16 20:30 ---
Tool:   N/A (planning decision)
Action: Evaluated SHARK-capture as method replicate for discriminative MEME
Reference: Chow et al. 2025, Protein Science. PMC11917139.
Rationale (initial): MEME benchmarked at ~20% recall on IDR SLiMs vs ~70%
  for SHARK-capture. If positive control MEME fails to detect spiked
  PxxP/RSxSP/SxTL motifs, SHARK-capture would replace MEME as primary method.

--- 2026-06-16 ~21:00 ---
Decision: SHARK-capture NOT used. Reasons:
  1. Design mismatch: SHARK-capture finds conserved k-mers across orthologous
     sequences (evolutionary conservation). NOT designed for discriminative
     case/control motif discovery. Cannot use our length-matched control IDRs.
  2. Positive control passed: MEME discriminative mode successfully detected
     all 4 spiked SLiM classes at E<0.05, validating the pipeline as-is.
     No need for replacement method.
  3. No public web server: URL from paper (shark-capture.biocomp.unibo.it)
     did not resolve (net::ERR_NAME_NOT_RESOLVED). Only local CLI via
     pip install bio-shark, which requires orthologous input format.
  4. Appropriate design: MEME discriminative + PSP + length-matched controls
     is a fundamentally different (and more appropriate) design for
     case/control motif discovery than SHARK-capture's conservation-based
     approach.
Impact: Bootstrap stability test (8.2) used as primary validation instead.

