  - Threshold: 6th highest score in full set (58.90 bits)
Results:
  - Motif detected in 98.6% of bootstraps (threshold ≥90% for STABLE)
  - Mean sites per bootstrap: 4.8 (SD=2.2)
  - ≥3 sites in 85.0% of bootstraps
  - Full set: 6 sites
Verdict: STABLE — Motif 3 robustly detected in autism IDRs
Output: 03-analysis/bootstrap-results.csv

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Phase 7: Fisher's Exact Test Enrichment
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

--- 2026-06-16 22:00 ---
Tool:   09-enrichment-test.py
Action: Fisher's exact test for all 10 MEME motifs
Input:  03-analysis/meme.xml (10 motif PWMs with bayes_thresholds)
        00-raw/autism-idrs-clean.fasta (1502 seqs)
        01-control-data/control-idrs-clean.fasta (1130 seqs)
Method:
  - Extract probability matrix from MEME XML, convert to log-odds PWM via
    background frequencies from --sequences-- (order 0)
  - Scan each IDR with sliding window; best score >= bayes_threshold -> motif present
  - Build 2x2 contingency table per motif
  - One-sided Fisher's exact test (greater enrichment in autism)
  - Benjamini-Hochberg FDR correction (q < 0.05)
  - Effect sizes: odds ratio, enrichment fold
Results:
  Motif 1 (poly-H, E=3.1e-31): 12/1502 vs 0/1130, OR=inf, p=0.0012, q=0.0059  ***
  Motif 2 (poly-Q, E=7.1e-25): 41/1502 vs 7/1130, OR=4.5, p=2.2e-05, q=0.00022 ***
  Motif 3 (MSTTIMETTTTMATT):    6/1502 vs 0/1130, OR=inf, p=0.034,  q=0.086
  Motif 4 (DESRNYISNSAQSNG):    6/1502 vs 0/1130, OR=inf, p=0.034,  q=0.086
  Motif 5-10:                   not significant
  Notes: Only poly-Q and poly-H survive FDR. Motif 3 nominally significant
  but q=0.086. Poly-Q has strongest signal: 4.4x fold enrichment, OR=4.5.
Output: 03-analysis/enrichment-results.csv
